text:
my daughter @ohheylil posted this and while i agree üíØ i so wish that for her it wasn‚Äôt so personal; as it is for me and my youngest daughter. in my household all three of us can #metoo. 
the dialogue among fellow followers of jesus that we‚Äôve seen on social media and in our circles of influence has caused all of us to have to relive some of the worst moments of our lives. it‚Äôs also produced profound sadness that somehow those that have the ability to listen to the holy spirit can spew out such falsehood and unkindness. 
things i‚Äôve heard: 
if it were true why didn‚Äôt she report it? 
if it were true how come she can‚Äôt remember details?
if it were true why did she go back to 10 other parties?
none of those are valid questions to apply to a woman who is sharing her story of abuse decades after the fact. 
here are a few facts.
in 1982 when someone that you knew attacked you sexually it was not called rape. frankly we didn‚Äôt know what to call it and we just assumed that we were dirty girls that put ourselves in bad situations and that we deserved what we got.
which is the same answer as to why we can‚Äôt remember the details because we tried to block it out of our minds as the incident was surrounded in self shame and sorrow for lost innocence. it also is the answer for why we would go back to the same party where they were again or even date him again or allow them in our house again because we had no idea that what happened to us was not our fault but that they were an abuser and that we were a victim. galatians 6:2
#bekind #lovegodlovepeople #jesuslovesme #metoo #myhelpcomesfromthelord

text: i wasn‚Äôt sexually assaulted in the typical ‚Äúpenis penetrating me‚Äù way, but that didn‚Äôt take away the panic attacks that came after a man‚Äôs head went anywhere near my lower body. i wasn‚Äôt sexualized by my neighbors in the stereotypical way, nor were they all adults. i didn‚Äôt know why i was so uncomfortable yet wanting to be acknowledged. i hate that i‚Äôve been going back and forth wondering why i had panic attacks when reflecting on it, was it even ‚Äúbad‚Äù or ‚Äúlegitimate?‚Äù i wasn‚Äôt abused by a partner in the stereotypical way, but it didn‚Äôt make it any less traumatizing. i never use this account, i guess i don‚Äôt have to explain myself but i want to be able to organize the shit in my head. i hate that i didn‚Äôt take time to heal after certain things because i convinced myself it was just my anxiety. it‚Äôs a lot to take in at once. it‚Äôs important to know that your experiences are valid. your trauma is valid. i wish i had known these things while they were happening. üíñüíñ #metoo #mentalhealth #anxiety #ptsd #yourtraumaisvalid #depression #fear #edrecovery #recovery #warrior #wearenotalone #youarenotalone

i would  encourage women to speak up and find freedom in telling their stories, timing is everything, today our stories matter, we matter and can find great healing knowing we are not alone. i will use this month to tell my story and open platforms for others to tell theirs. we never deserved what happened to us and i think today we became more aware of this and just want to shout "yes, it happened to me too!" let our little voices be heard without fear, there is support on a global level and it's our time!

text_retweet:
over the past couple of days i've experienced and heard a bunch of upsetting things: from highschool boys talking inappropriately and objectifying¬† their female classmates and people excusing them by saying "boys will be boys," "they are just joking it's not serious," etc., to people reposting an upsetting image of what feminism should look like and what it shouldn't, to unknown men harassing me on the street and getting mad when i don't respond flirtatiously,¬† to¬† the kavanaugh hearing, which shows an extreme and deeply upsetting example of the systemic oppressions all women face, all the time and how no matter what we do we/women are always on trial. 
so i decided to post this selfie so that i can (hopefully) help erase the stigma around the female body. my body is natural, my body is beautiful, my body is deserving of respect, my body is mine, and no you do not have the right to touch it, objectify it, or use it in anyway you please without my approval and consent. just bc i'm in my underwear in this picture does not mean i'm a slut, a attention seeker, or that "i'm asking for it." its simply bc i love myself, i embrace all of me every perfection & imperfection, & bc to me it's an empowering feminist act. 
men need to start taking responsibility for their actions and start treating us like actual human beings and not like some sex toys. men & boys need to start being help accountable for the pain, disrespect & discomfort they cause us on a daily basis. (and yes ofc not all men but unfortunately the majority have at some point in their life mistreated a woman, and it's become such a norm that most men don't even realise it and most women are to afraid and uncomfortable to point it out). i call on every woman (or any person really who¬† feels the same) to also post a "risky" picture in order to eliminate the taboo, which is the female body. 
p.s. if you disagree & judge me feel free to unfollow me! this is a negative free zone, however i am always up for respectful discussions on your views & beliefs üíõ

text:
trump orders fbi to investigate kavanaugh before full senate votes
@qz / simone stolzoff

donald trump has directed the fbi to investigate the sexual-assault allegations against his us supreme court nominee brett kavanaugh.

kavanaugh has been accused by¬†multiple women¬†of sexual misconduct, including christine blasey ford, who testified before the senate judiciary committee. the nominee denies any wrongdoing regarding ford or any other women. ‚Äúi‚Äôve ordered the fbi to conduct a supplemental investigation to update judge kavanaugh‚Äôs file,‚Äù trump said in a statement today (sept. 28). ‚Äúas the senate has requested, this update must be limited in scope and completed in less than one week.‚Äù the order came just hours after kavanaugh‚Äôs nomination¬†was approved¬†by the committee¬†in 11-10 vote along party lines. however, senator jeff flake, a republican from arizona, made it clear that he would not vote for kavanaugh on the senate floor without an fbi investigation of the allegations against him. republican senators lisa murkowski of alaska and susan collins of maine backed flake‚Äôs push for a one-week delay on a floor vote.

a lawyer for mark judge,¬†kavanaugh‚Äôs friend who ford says was¬†in the room when the alleged assault occurred in 1982, said today his client ‚Äúwill answer any and all questions posed to him‚Äù by the fbi. though judge has previously denied any recollection of the event in question, he also has admitted to abusing alcohol in high school.

full story in bio link üëÜ üì∑: executive office of the president of the united states / wikimedia commons

text:
please, stop raising your children as they have to do specific things in their lives. cleaning the house and cooking doesn't make a woman more woman. stop making your daughter think she has to learn to do those things because "she's a woman". teach her that doing that is just a way to help in home. stop making her think she can't wear shorts because that's something that only sluts do. do not make her think she has to stay at home and be a housewife to be a good wife. do not definitely serve men more food because "men eat more than women do". do not make your son think he has to let his wife do all the house work while he watches the football match. teach him to cook for her if she is tired or sick. don't teach him he has to be "the king of the house", teach him he's part of the family so he has to be able to help everytime his help is required. tell him to respect his wife when she's not in the mood or exhausted.

change starts at home.

text:
i woke up from a dream where i was walking down the hallway in my elementary school around 2:30 a.m.. i immediately thought about this picture (swipe) because it‚Äôs always kind of haunted me. i then thought about teddy graham graham crackers and immediately felt sick to my stomach from sheer anxiety. i remember my mom being so upset that i hadn‚Äôt taken off the gray vest to show my pink shirt (it had dogs playing with doggy bones on it). she had carefully rummaged through the bins of donated shirts in our church‚Äôs basement to find a an outfit worthy of a school picture we couldn‚Äôt afford. she had sacrificed everything to move us here a couple of months prior. i had already lost my father to alcoholism and jail. i look at this picture and i‚Äôm haunted by the turmoil in my eyes and the effort it must have taken me to contort my face into that heartbreaking attempt at a smile. that‚Äôs because when this picture was taken, at five and a half years old, i was already a survivor of prolonged sexual abuse. she marked the back ‚Äúmemories of kindergarten‚Äù. i don‚Äôt think we had the same thing in mine when she wrote that on the back.

this memory is one of countless others that haunted me every single time my ex-husband (@hornhornhornhorn ) told me to go drink about my sexual assault and kill myself. this black square is the emptiness i have felt inside for so long and the void i hope others would feel if i had ever followed through.

text: like a bad thread that has been woven into the tapestry of my life, these moments in my past blend in. are mostly forgotten. every story i read that triggers a long forgotten memory compels me to re-examine those frayed edges. and as i pull on the end of that black thread, i find the same narrative at the end, each time. the unwanted touches. unwanted words. unwanted exposure. from men when i was only a little girl. i deserved them. i asked for them. since there was a sad and lonely part of me that liked the attention for a moment, i deserved when it went too far. because my shorts were too short. because i was walking home alone. i went into that house on my own accord. i chose those friends. i went to that party. it was me. it was my fault. and in the end, nothing major happened...right? an adult, i can pull back the vail and see clearly the lies society had taught me all along. that sexual assault isn‚Äôt anything major. that a grown man pursuing a young girl means she must be desirable, not that he is a disgusting pig. that it is the girl‚Äôs choice to wear something that may attract unwanted attention, therefore, her fault when a man does more than look. that if a girl chooses to put herself in that situation, she plays a part in the abuse inflicted upon her. and as i sit here in my bed at 2 in the morning, with the words from another woman haunting my mind, i realize for the very first time in my life that i have not one but many, many, many #metoo moments cleverly tucked away throughout my life. and i‚Äôm shocked. i‚Äôm 35 years old. i have a daughter. i teach young children. i‚Äôve been living with these lies my whole life. allowing them to lull me into an ignorant stupor. but i‚Äôm awake now. and it‚Äôll change everything.

text:
instead of disappearing for a day, being bold and speaking loudly resonates with me more.  when my fianc√© and i (now husband) took this set of photos a decade ago, it caused a small outrage.  not with our parents or my grandmother (who admired them)... but with the public.  i loved them then and love them now.  for the record:
i am a sensual being and a daughter
i am a mother and a lover
i am demure and outrageous
i am fearful and fearless
i am weak and i am extraordinary
i am right and i am wrong
i am a totality. 
so are you.
so are we all ...and i'm not going away.

text: today is my birthday and i spent the weekend well (mmm, charred octopus tentacle!)... i‚Äôll enjoy it until my husband leaves to help my parents with the iowa corn and soybean harvest soon. we will miss him so much but those roots from the family farm are what has made me hearty and strong. it makes me sad this time of year, though, because i‚Äôve had to cut some of that farm family out of my life... i‚Äôm a happier person for it, absolutely, but i miss some days when comparisons and envy and politics didn‚Äôt muddle it all. an artist, i am very liberal leaning, as you might imagine. and they simply aren‚Äôt. i can‚Äôt blame anyone for wanting to live and love freely, colorfully, and doing all of that while having a strong social safety net. every note and comment of mine was fought with a dense, negative hatred that got too dark for me. i had to say that it was enough. it takes a lot to respect yourself and in the #metoo space, i feel buoyed and not as alone as i could be. it took 36 years to get here and i love where the path of high vibrations and light is leading... thanks for sharing it with me üí´

.

text:
italian actress asia argento, who became a leading figure in the #metoo movement after accusing powerful hollywood producer harvey weinstein of rape, admitted she had sex with young actor jimmy bennett, who claimed she sexually assaulted him as a teenager.

during a television show in italy on sunday argento, who had initially denied having sex with bennett, recounted her relationship with the actor.

argento, who played his troubled mother in the 2004 film ‚Äúthe heart is deceitful above all things,‚Äù saw him again in may 2013, when he was 17 and she was 37.

according to bennett‚Äôs account of the encounter he gave in a september 24 interview on italian television, argento kissed him for a long time. ‚Äúit turned into her placing her hands on me and following that was when she pushed me onto the bed and took my pants off,‚Äù said the actor, now 22.

asked whether it was a ‚Äúcomplete‚Äù relationship, bennett said it was, implying they had sex, but declined to go into detail.

the actor and rock musician was 17 years old at the time of the alleged assault. the legal age of consent in california is 18.

argento strongly denied his version of events, saying the young man had asked her to help him prepare for an audition, as she did when he was a child. ‚Äúhe started kissing me and touching me, but not as a mother and child as i saw him, but as a boy with raging hormones ‚Ä¶ and that froze me,‚Äù she recounted.

#elixirng #metoo #italy #asiaargento #harveyweinstein #jimmybennett #hollywood

text: what an inspiring afternoon @raindancefilmfestival ‚Äòan open letter to the industry: filmmaking after #timesup ‚Äò an amazing, eye-opening panel of women all fighting for equality, representation and justice. having had my own experience in a casting room, this really resonated with me. the director for an apparently ‚Äòbig-budget‚Äô movie asked me to straddle him. when i refused, he smacked me extremely hard on the arse. i had the confidence to stand up to him but many wouldn‚Äôt. i hate how those in power think they can get away with episodes like this. i really do hope time‚Äôs up indeed. unfortunately, even though the company were removed from the casting website, they appeared again this year. again, they were removed because i had seen the job and reported it, but where else was it advertised? it‚Äôs scary to think how many women have been through this. thanks to @denparkinson #samantharennie #rosafund @abenat_s #denalitiller @gabereau & @raindancefilmfestival for bringing this conversation #timesup #metoo #raindance #raindancefilmfestival #rosafund #justiceandequalityfund #womeninfilm #actor #actress #casting #womenfilmmakers #film #movie #womenempowerment

text:
i don't know what to write here.
because i have so much to say.
i have so many tears to cry as i type this out,i have a sore throat from all the screaming i've been doing.
i did my last post & got such an overwhelming response.
i didn't want that.i didn't want people to relate to this.i didn't want to know how many of us are swimming in this pool of pain.
i went crazy.i talked about it everywhere.
i screamed all over.
and i still am,and not for a minute,will this screaming ever stop,until the harassment does.
i'll make this more of a feedback post,for all the questions i got.
what made you post this?
because i'm a victim,and i'm done staying silent & empowering these perpetrators.
is every man like this?
no.some are truly good.and my next post will be on this.
what can we do,and how can we protect ourselves?
we scream.we get the attention of the masses that have neglected us.
protection (and i wish i wasn't writing this),it's the small things.
@minisokenya sell small spray bottles in affordable packs.you can get one,or even just from the street,and mix black pepper (au pilipili shamba) with water & carry it.if someone tries to take advantage of you,spray them in the eye.
i will not tell you not to go out,drink & have fun.i won't tell you not to wear short dresses.i won't tell you to constantly walk with a male companion as a bodyguard.i will not forbid you from enjoying yourself,this world is as much yours as it is theirs.
also,keys can be an amazing defence.
now,can the government help?
can the ministry of education introduce self-defence classes at a young age?to everyone?
can they teach our young boys how to respect females?
can we make the penalty for rape and sexual harassment,no matter how mild,a life sentence with no parole?
can we get proper channels to follow in the case of an incident?
because it has to stop.we have to be better.we have to scream!!! (a big thanks to @ku999fm for having me on the carribean show to scream some more.) #canwegetahotline
#enough
#metoo
#notalone

text:
ladies of america...thank you for standing up and making your voices heard! i admire your courage, commitment, and strength. that's what you project everyday as leaders, mothers, educators, doctors, ceo's, professional athletes, scientists, lawyers, healthcare workers, law enforcement, service members, fitness instructors, pilots, students, and so many more occupations. you nurture, you care, and you move this world in the right direction for us with all of the contributions you make. you create life for us!  on many levels you are stronger and more deserving of greatness than men. i recognize this and truly believe that. i believe that so much that i marched side by side with you during the women's march with a great deal of pride. it's time for all men to recognize that too. your time has come. seize this moment in solidarity and don't look back! only foward. the momentum is on your side! don't ever let anyone tell you that you can have you what you're fighting for. you are the change you've been waiting for. i support you 100%!
- mike l

text:
my earliest memory of feeling uncomfortable with a boy's behavior (#violation) was before i was five years old. my parents were still married and hanging upstairs with another couple, while i was playing legos or something with their son (of similar age). the boy, blonde with a bowl cut just like mine, disinterested in legos proceeds to chase me around trying to take off my clothes and kiss me... seeming to be imitating what he saw on #daytimesoaps ... #whatever #ididntlikeit #ididntwanthimto yet he wouldnt leave me alone. eventually i escaped and proceeded to tell on him to both our sets of parents.
both moms and dads just laughted saying "boys will be boys" #wtf this was maybe 1980 but now! 
and ok the legos may be an additional detail added to the story, but his behavior was very real!
#boyswillbeboys #hellno #metoo #believeher #christineblaseyford #truth
#smashthepatriarchy #sickandtired #kavanaugh

text:
i can‚Äôt seem to fall asleep tonight without sharing. i was 17 and on a road trip with my best friend. we went to see her brother play baseball. one night after a game there was a party. it was late and there was underage drinking going on. i was nervous so i told my friend, who wanted to stay, that i was going to sleep. i left the party and went back to the room we were staying in and tried to sleep. i woke up to someone crawling into bed with me. i thought it was my friend but it wasn‚Äôt. it was her brother. i remember feeling paralyzed. i remember feeling his penis press into my back and him putting his hands on me. i blamed myself. i remember thinking how could i have put myself in this situation and that it must have been something i did or said. i remember shutting my eyes and praying he‚Äôd leave. why i didn‚Äôt scream or kick or get up- i don‚Äôt know. why did i not make a big deal of it? he was my best friend‚Äôs brother, a star athlete and one of the nicest, funniest guys in our church youth group. i trusted him, and told myself that he was just drunk. 
here i am, 11 years later, and i wish that girl had known one truth: it‚Äôs not your fault.

text:
leaving all the "politicalness" out of this post. leaving it far far behind. i want to speak to you today, purely about the trauma of sexual assault. i am compassionately hurting for victims of sexual abuse everywhere tonight who are reliving their worst nightmares over and over again because what is happening in the news. i am also devastated by the lack of knowledge that surrounds the recurring impact it continues to have on our society. ever further more, i am shocked at the ignorance that is out there of impact trauma leaves on the human brain and body. soooo...it is time to be educated social media world, of course with lots of love, because that is how this should be done <3 
first, according to the national sexual violence resource center (nsvrc): -one in five women and one in 71 men will be raped at some point in their lives -in the u.s., one in three women and one in six men experienced some form of contact sexual violence in their lifetime -51.1% of female victims of rape reported being raped by an intimate partner and 40.8% by an acquaintance -52.4% of male victims report being raped by an acquaintance and 15.1% by a stranger -almost half (49.5%) of multiracial women and over 45% of american indian/alaska native women were subjected to some form of contact sexual violence in their lifetime -91% of victims of rape and sexual assault are female, and nine percent are male -in eight out of 10 cases of rape, the victim knew the perpetrator -8 % of rapes occur while the victim is at work 
now let's talk briefly about trauma.

effects of sexual violence quoted from rainn's webpage (rainn stands for (rape, abuse, incest, national network): -sexual violence can have psychological, emotional, and physical effects on a survivor. - depression -flashbacks -self harm -eating disorders -unwanted pregnancy - std‚Äôs
-sleep disorders
-suicides

if you would like more information about rainn or the services they offer to victims of sexual abuse, learn more at their webpage.

continued in next posts... #kellythoughts #sexualassault #metoo #whyididntreport #whyididntspeak #trauma #kellyairhart #artherapy

text:
#continuedpost  i hope you are still with me. i hope that you care and want to learn so you can be better and speak with compassion, judge less, and love more. sexual assault is no joke. it leaves families broken. it leaves women and men feeling worthless and shamed. it is a heavy weight to carry as a victim. i hope by giving these women a safe place to share their stories i open your minds and hearts. i hope we can all be better and do better.

over 90% of reported sexual abuse cases are real. don't let the 10% overpower the truth. they don't deserve that kind of power. we deserve to be heard. women and men, we stand together!

i am sharing with you now, real stories from women who shared with me. they asked to remain anonymous, so these artistic renderings do not reflect the actual victims in any way.

keep safe. know that you are loved no matter what and i am here for you. let's change the world together. <3 ‚Äúbc he was a man of authority and i was told all my life i was nothing." #whyididntspeak

#kellythoughts #metoo #whyididntspeak #voicesrising #believesurvivors #whyididntreport #trauma #kellyairhart #arttherapy #truestory #notmine

text:
yesterday the smell of a cinnamon apple candle sent me reeling. i ran home and showered and doused perfume in my hair. but nothing, fucking nothing could get that smell out. i was in my bed, in my college dorm, a part of me you‚Äôve never touched. but my body‚Äî 
my body was shaking. 
my body is still under you, 
even after all these years. 
#metoo

text:
it's with a heavy heart but hope for a brighter future that i share my story with you. there are a crushing number of women, children, and men with stories of their own.
i was a little girl and the few people i told either didn't believe me or dismissed it as "not that bad." for years i tried to bury the memories, i sometimes wondered if i really did make it up or it was something that was just a nightmare that i made real in my head. the memories are some of the most vivid memories of my entire childhood.
it wasn't until spring of my freshman year of high school that i had a conversation with one of my sisters about it. she was shocked and angry. that conversation sparked a domino effect that led to it being reported to the police. i remember leaving school early several times so that i could go to the downtown police building and talk with officers and the prosecutor. i lied to classmates about where i was going.
the hearings continued for about a year and a half after that. i accepted plea deal for 6 months in jail, along with him being a registered sex offender as well as receiving therapy. i choose that option in hopes that it would save others from what i went through. he got off on "good behavior" after 4 months. 
my high school years were extremely hard, all i wanted was to fit in while i felt so far removed from everyone. i developed a substance abuse problem and started heavily drinking at the age of 14. i became depressed and suicidal.
it was not my choice to report it, but i'm glad i did. i wouldn't say it gave me closure, but it did give me validation. validation that what i went through was real, it was wrong, and there were people who believed me and would help me seek justice.
we need to stop victim blaming, we need to stop supporting abusers in power, and we need to listen, especially to those with the quietest voices. i'm one of the only people i know who went through the prosecution process and that needs to change. #ibelieveher #ibelievedrford #time'sup #metoo

text: i really can‚Äôt stress this. all this crap with kavanaugh has brought up a lot for me... a lot of stuff that i thought i had processed... i‚Äôm back to wearing my hair in a ponytail, i can‚Äôt wear a lanyard at work anymore, i don‚Äôt even wear my necklace with my moms signature on it... and why? because the thing that assaulted me grabbed my neck... it took me 6 years to process all of that and let things touch my neck... my hair became thin from how much i wear it up. you ask why don‚Äôt report... i tried... no one believed me... my own best friends didn‚Äôt believe me. how can we hang on to something for so long? because we are conditioned to believe we deserved it, then we find people along our paths that remind us we didn‚Äôt and we have to do it all over again... why do we speak up when someone is at this point in their career? because someone like that doesn‚Äôt need any more power than what he has taken from us... you wanna know why we don‚Äôt report look in the mirror you‚Äôre probably part of the problem #metoo #10yearslater #mystory #whyididntreport #itriedtoreport if you didn‚Äôt know this about me there‚Äôs a good chance you didn‚Äôt know anyone else‚Äôs... this isn‚Äôt something i wanna grab coffee and discuss this is something i use to help myself and others... you are never at fault for saying no! #theabsenceofnodoesnotmeanyes #absenceofno

text: as i read about people disgustingly criticizing dr.ford for not remembering certain things about that night. to start, she is someone i look up to for being brave enough to speak out, so many survivors who haven't spoken up because of fear. fear that you are lying, that it didn't happen because you were young. they pick and pull your sexual assault account and brush it off by saying sorry it didn't happen because it doesn't add up. how dare anybody try to tell someone what did or didn't happen to them. i have struggled myself to watch dr. ford take the stand for my personal reasons and watching her speak made tear up. but i finally did it and as a survivor myself i take her story to heart and applaud her forever for being so brave. thank you dr.christine blasey ford for giving me the courage to acknowledge that i am a survivor publicly even posting this is difficult,but i do it for anyone else who is a survivor. #metoo #braveryiscontagious

i have lived through countless situations where i was made to do things, one way or another, that i did not want to happen to my body. 
i've been cornered and groped
pinned to the wall by a man significantly larger than me
manipulated into allowing countless sexual acts for years because it was easier than fighting and/or i was scared i'd lose everything if i didn't. 
all different ages, different situations, different people. since basically highschool. 
don't tell me it's innocent fun
don't tell me it doesn't matter

as it was for all of us, this week was truly a rollercoaster of emotions. after talking with friends about the week and our lives as women in general, the overall consensus was the we were exhausted. exhausted from feeling that our voices are not being heard. exhausted from fear, rage and sadness. exhausted from fighting for our rights. but dr. ford re-lit a fire in women across the country. watching her testimony was heartbreaking, infuriating, and inspiring. she is a hero for women and more importantly a hero for survivors.
i spent this weekend taking a much needed mental and physical health break. spent a lot of time focusing on things that bring me joy...singing, calligraphy, photography, rancho alegre, and wine. now, i am well rested and ready to jump back in the fightüí™üèº

text:
today marks #domesticviolenceawarenessmonth
as a #survivor i strive everyday to not allow my past to define me. to make moves that are reflective of whom god would call me to be. to never be held back by someone else‚Äôs wants and opinions. it wasn‚Äôt just physical for me. it was emotional, it was sexual, it was mental, it was verbal, it was financial. i know the feeling of being dragged, choked, grabbed, slapped, having a gun held to me, sleeping with a gun in our bed, being name called, my money being withheld and demanded, told where i could work and for how long, who i could hang with, who i could talk to, what to wear and not wear, what my own children could/couldn‚Äôt do, when to have sex regardless of if it hurt physically or i didn‚Äôt want to, being able to go to school or even complete school, being accused of going places or doing things i didn‚Äôt do all because it didn‚Äôt measure up to his ‚Äústandards‚Äù and this was just in the relationship. flash to now...the narcissistic patterns still exists. having a child with someone whom you‚Äôve been abused by but not even with is hard. but god!!! the woman i am today is because all that he did to break me developed me into a strong #unbreakable person.
.
.
#gaslighting #metoo #abuseisreal #abuse #dv #domesticviolence #bruisedbutnotbroken #physicalabuse #sexualabuse #emotionalabuse #verbalabuse #btsadv

text:
i meant to post this a few days ago, in support of #christineblaseyford and her bravery. teal is the color chosen to show support for sexual assault awareness. 
these past few weeks have been so draining, mentally & emotionally. i go back & forth between feeling empowered & feeling hopeless. it was nearly impossible to not get triggered by the events in the news & commentary. in spite of trying to take care of myself i still found myself curled up in the fetal position the other night, feeling nauseous, & trying not to cry.
overall i have hope in how things are slowly moving in the right direction. i am empowered by the number of people (women & men) who have come forward to bravely share their stories. i am grateful for the support of others for this #metoo movement and for those of us who are survivors. i hope someday to see a world where we no longer have to say #metoo, where women aren‚Äôt thought of as less than men.
#survivor #sexualassaultawareness #bravery #courage #notavictim #balance #yogashapes #innerstrength #phoenixrising #ibelieveher #believesurvivors #trauma #traumahealing

text:
fresh face #sunday. today, many women changed their profile photo across social media platforms to a black square, to represent a world with out women....but i don‚Äôt want to be in a world without women, and i‚Äôm not a black square. i want us to show the world what it‚Äôs like to live with us when we are strong, empowered, and ready to make change so our daughters don‚Äôt have to #metoo and bury secrets. 
i don‚Äôt want to be told i‚Äôm too loud, i talk too much, i don‚Äôt dress ‚Äúlike a lady‚Äù, my hair is too bright, i don‚Äôt ‚Äúfit in‚Äù etc...because i love and celebrate all those things daily and have worked my ass off to get to this place of self acceptance. in a world constantly putting us down and telling who we should be, loving ourselves and being proud of who we are isn‚Äôt always easy, some days it‚Äôs damn near impossible. 
i am here to shine bright, this world needs my light and i‚Äôm not gonna dim it for anyone. 
love and support to all my sisters, participating in the ‚Äú blackout‚Äù or not, too loud or too quite, struggling or thriving. you are not alone, you are loved, your light is needed and you are here to shine.

#shinebright #shineyourlight #liveyourtruth #beyou #beyoutiful #loveyourself

text:
hey #yoga friends: starting monday, october 1st, i‚Äôm re-donating all the donations received for my monday evening donation-based yoga classes to the ‚Äúlong road to recovery‚Äù #gofundme campaign. my friend rachel‚Äôs son was shot at a #kcmo bar after standing up to a dude who was harassing his girlfriend, and the funds raised will assist with his expenses during recovery. i‚Äôll post the full story in the comments, but here‚Äôs why doing this is important to me: i am angry just like you are. we are all angry, regardless of how we side on the issues surrounding the current socio-political landscape. i mean, i‚Äôve never wanted to burn it all to the ground more in my entire life, but i don‚Äôt truly believe that angry actions heal. i want to, instead, direct my energy into the appreciation i have for nathan‚Äôs respect and bravery, as well as rachel (@voleraerial ), for raising a couple noble-ass sons with more conviction in their veins than complacency. i invite you to join us for the weekly practice, or to donate on your own thru @gofundme . class details in the pic. all levels welcome, bring your own mat & towel. warning: there are free roaming cats.
.
.

text:
mmmk here is some #sobermom #realtalk for ya.
‚Ä¢
‚Ä¢
i love my daughter. she blows my mind. she enhances my life. she is the greatest, deepest, sweetest, truest love i have ever known. the day she was born i was altered on a deep, cellular, fundamental level. the things that were important before weren‚Äôt anymore and i believe my destiny was sent on an entirely different trajectory in the instant they laid her perfect little 6lb 12oz body on my chest. ‚Ä¢
‚Ä¢
but. something has remained unchanged. and that is my alcoholism. my daughter is not enough to keep me sober. it is hard saying that and sometimes it makes me cringe. because i so don‚Äôt want it to be true. i want her to be enough to ‚Äúcure‚Äù me. but she just isn‚Äôt. because this cunning and baffling dis-ease that is centred in my brain is stronger than that love, unless i take the daily actions in my life to treat it. ‚Ä¢
‚Ä¢
i came terrifyingly close to a drink after she was born. i stopped prioritizing my spiritual connection and fell into the mind trap that she was all i needed. i stopped going to meetings, praying & meditating and doing service. i started noticing the liquor stores. i reached for a beer at one point. ‚Ä¢
‚Ä¢
here is the thing i have learned from that. when i take the time to prioritize and nuture my connection (to self, heart, others, source) i get the privilege of showing up not only physically, but emotionally and spiritually as well. when i do these things and stay sober the possibilities are endless. if i drink there are no possibilities. self care as a mother is crucial. self care as a sober mom is vital. take care of you too, warrior mamas. the babes need and deserve the best you. ‚Ä¢
‚Ä¢

text:
i was 27 and i stood up for myself. i didn‚Äôt do it just for me but for any woman that would have to be in his presence. i was scared but felt supported by the men and women i worked with. i was scared he would come after me because i made him lose his job. 
and then he returned to the same program with the same company i worked for this time. i stood up for myself and the other women again and it was handled quickly and quietly. 
and then not more than 6 months later he showed up again. we started on the same day on a new program with the same company. this time we had to rehash what happened when i was 27 because ‚Äúthey lost the records‚Äù or ‚Äúbecause we were both contractors, they didn‚Äôt keep track of it.‚Äù it took 3.5 weeks for them to decide what to do. their decision: we can‚Äôt work on the same program but he is welcome to work on campus on any other program. 
he apologized to them and asked that they pass his apology on to me. they excused what he did to me 8 years prior. 
i couldn‚Äôt protect myself or anyone else because they felt it was ok to go against their zero tolerance policy. they told us if we saw each other on campus we should walk the other way. as if this was supposed to make me feel safe or prevent either of us from feeling extremely uncomfortable. 
i left. my safety and sanity come first and foremost. not much later i left aerospace because i couldn‚Äôt change this mentality. i didn‚Äôt deserve to be objectified, sexually assaulted, sexually harassed, or demonized for being a woman ‚Äúin a man‚Äôs world‚Äù. so yeah, #metoo. stand up for yourself to stand up for others who have stayed silent. show them it‚Äôs the best thing for all of us.

text:
oh sacred feminine. how we have wronged you. from polluting our earth to denying your words, from paying you less to blaming you more, from running from our emotions to denying our intimate and vulnerable spaces within, we have a long way to go in how we treat the feminine within, and surrounding, us. ‚ù§Ô∏è
üíù
it‚Äôs been a very hard week for many of us. women, womxn, ladies, girls, mothers, sisters, and those that honor the female within. survivors. light bearers. noble knights. peaceful warriors. what a horrific trespass on so many of us, watching a woman reliving so much pain and trauma as if on behalf of us all, yet steeped in calm steadiness - the true #sanskrit notion of #sthira & #sukha, strong structure and graceful ease. how can we honor this push and pull in finding #balance in all corners of life, especially when so much feels out of our control?
how can we congregate and fight back with love, peace, equality - and win?
‚ù§Ô∏è
üíù
for starters, how can we worship the divine feminine in our own life, whether with the mother in all forms, the sister in all women, the ancestors in all teachers? the divine feminine represents the connection to the part of your consciousness responsible for nurture, intuition, and empathy, regardless of your gender. this is the aspect of the self associated with creation, intuition, community, sensuality, and collaboration. how can we collaborate, share, and feel into a new space of safety and peace for the divine feminine within ourselves and our communities to hopefully manifest into our political and professional arenas as well? ‚ù§Ô∏è
üíù
bowing in gratitude to #pachimama #lakshmi #kuanyin #aphrodite #kali #tara #yemaya #virginmary #marymagdalene and the mothers, daughters, aunties, and sisters. may we rise, unite, and organize in love üíóüë±‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏èüë©üèæüëµüèΩüë∏üèøüßôüèº‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏èü§∞üèªüíÉüèºüëØ‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏èüë©‚Äç‚ù§Ô∏è‚Äçüë©üë©‚Äçüëß‚Äçüë¶üíí

.
.
.
jill filipovic, the guardian

i thought well since men are bad #metoo but that was brokenness.

do not expect disney testimony's before a person is healed.

but you can expect one afterward. miracles are real.

text:
working in the theme of resurrection.

#mayaangelou

did you want to see me broken?
bowed head and lowered eyes?
shoulders falling down like teardrops,
weakened by my soulful cries?

does my haughtiness offend you?
don't you take it awful hard
'cause i laugh like i've got gold mines
diggin' in my own backyard.

you may shoot me with your words,
you may cut me with your eyes,
you may kill me with your hatefulness,
but still, like air, i'll rise.

#poetry #resist #art_seeking #art_4share #art_worldly

.
this week was filled with shock from events around the world, including south of the border about sexual assault.
.

we need to talk about it, hear the stories, and make everyone understand that women deserve human rights. 
thank you @omidfoundation in vancouver for your efforts and giving marginalized women in iran hope.
.
happy sunday! have a great week ahead!
.
-dr. z

text: i need to lay this down, as it were. this whole societal movement has brought to fore things i had held far distant from myself for decades. the girl in these pictures was sexually assaulted, molested, by a much older man. he grabbed her on a river bank full of children and felt her up and down for several minutes while she shivered, frozen, exhausted from a weekend of sun and canoeing on the colorado river for the better part of two days. she felt scared and betrayed. she didn‚Äôt know him, but he was savvy enough to do this out in the open while adults and children were milling around, putting canoes on trailers and dragging gear up from the shore on to vehicles in preparation for taking off. the girl suppressed her memories of this for several years until awakening on her 16th birthday realizing that the abject fear she had for men over the age of 20 came from this incident. yes, i told my folks right after it had happened. no charges were filed, & for years i worried i‚Äôd come upon this monster again. i have no closure. i just have this feeling of emptiness when i think about it. but knowing i‚Äôm not alone helps, and i have raised two sons who know my continuing pain stemming from this time in my life. i‚Äôve had abusive boyfriends, i‚Äôve done risky things and have been so lucky. but this incident marks a break in my childhood. one i dearly hope my daughter escapes. #metoo #belivesurvivors i was almost 13.

steinem added a huge caveat back then ‚Äï one that is painfully relevant at this moment, as the senate weighs the allegations against #kavanaugh: it typically takes more than one woman for an accusation to stick. in campus sexual assault cases, for example, steinem said, ‚Äúit takes four or five women accusing the same guy before it‚Äôs believed.‚Äù indeed, in almost all the most high-profile me too cases ‚Äï harvey weinstein, les moonves, charlie rose, matt lauer ‚Äï it took more than one woman to bring down a single man, no matter how credible the accusation. in other words, *yes*, women are being believed ‚Äï but it‚Äôs not entirely clear that a woman will be found credible. particularly when she‚Äôs going up against the pinnacle of american male power ‚Äï a prep school and ivy league-educated lawyer with immense political connections. kavanaugh‚Äôs supporters were out in full force on monday attacking blasey ford‚Äôs credibility, just as hill was attacked decades ago. thomas‚Äô ascension to the court triggered a wave of women running for office. just as pussy-grabber-in-chief trump‚Äôs election spurred women‚Äôs marches, inspired more women to run for office and, arguably, galvanized the me too movement. and yet, for all that, we‚Äôre somehow back to a 1990s-style moment. what happens next will be a test to see how far we‚Äôve come ‚Äï have women gained real credibility? but why should my freedom be offending? .
.
.
.
.

stripped.
i have been overly sexualized most of my teenage and adult life.
i have been single for 4 years almost and to be completely honest i am super alone and bare.

as a leo i rarely let down my guard and show my emotional rollercoasters, but right now in my life i have lost my rose colored glasses.
may we all feel the raw depths of our human existence to comprehend and eventually rise from the ashes.
this song makes me sob. its real and beautiful and painful.
it has been so powerful to see the support for everyone sharing thier vulnerable stories and allies speaking out to help others suffering of mental ilnesses and challenges.
this is a peice of my soul.

text:
boyz. you do not grab girls. ‚†Ä ‚†Ä
if it‚Äôs not mutual.
‚†Ä
you do not grab me if i‚Äôm russian, chinese, indian, american, italian, or any other nationality. 
you do not grab me if you‚Äôve heard a stereotype that ‚Äúrussians are sluts‚Äù. wrong.
‚†Ä
you do not grab me just because you want it. i do not want it. 
you do not grab me as if i‚Äôm a candy bar on a shelf. i am not a candy. even if you call me sweet. i am not a thing. i am a person. 
you do not grab me even if i wear a short dress. it does not mean anything. it is not a sign. it is not a ‚Äúgreen light‚Äù. you respect my personal space. you respect my rights. you do not grab me.
‚†Ä
you do not grab me even if i asked you to drive me home. you do not have any rights to grab me just because i am in your car. i am not going to thank you for driving me with allowing grabbing me. no. wrong.
‚†Ä
you do not depreciate me just because you are a male and you are ‚Äústronger‚Äù. the fact that i am a girl, and the society labeled me as ‚Äúweaker‚Äù than you does not mean that you have a right to grab me. no-one has a right to grab me.
‚†Ä
i am a human being, just like you. girls are not worse or any better than boys. we are all equal. you don‚Äôt want to be grabbed, don‚Äôt you? so don‚Äôt grab me.
‚†Ä
i am a female just like your mom and your daughter. would you be fine if someone grabs your mom or daughter? no.
‚†Ä
you don‚Äôt grab me because you assume i want it. just because i am in your car or house does not mean in any ways that you own the moment. i‚Äôm trusting myself to you when i sit in your car. why should i be afraid to be grabbed by you? why should it be even a thing to worry about? why you are not afraid of me while staying one by one? just because you are a male? but it‚Äôs wrong. it is very wrong.
‚†Ä
all people are equal. we all should feel secure while staying in the same place with different genders. your sexual organ does not define you. it does not give you any privileges, it does not make you any good or bad, strong or weak, smart or dumb. i‚Äôm so sad that people mix up definitions of sexual organ and mind.
‚†Ä
my heart is sad that in our 21st century being afraid of a male is still a thing.
‚†Ä
so, please, give me a huge favor. don‚Äôt grab me.

text:
we believe and stand with survivors. period.
.
no one gets to decide when it‚Äôs ‚Äúappropriate‚Äù for a survivor of sexual assault to speak up.
.
exceptüëèüèºtheüëèüèæsurvivorüëèüèø
.
we stand against those trying to dictate this narrative or police women‚Äôs response to trauma when they haven‚Äôt taken any of the necessary steps to educate themselves on or fight against toxic masculinity and pervasive violence against women.
.
but most importantly, we are here to lift each other up, validate our experiences, and fight to stop all violence against women.
.
to do that well, addressing the complexities and intersections of our experiences and the systems we‚Äôre operating from is imperative. if dr. ford, a white, affluent, respected woman, who has demonstrated great courage and yet, has such a challenging time being believed, imagine the barriers that women of color and immigrant women, confronting destructive policies and racist attitudes must overcome, to be believed.
.
27 years after anita hill testified we are still having the same conversation- but we will not forget where we came from and who has paved the path before us.
.
so, whatever happens with the #kavanaughconfirmation, just take a breath, remember that we will keep fighting to create a safer and more just world for everyone.üíï
.

text:
‚Äúours is not the task of fixing the entire world at once, but of stretching out to mend the part of the world that is within our reach.‚Äù ‚Äî #clarissapinkolaestes ‚Ä¢

last week really was a week, wasn‚Äôt it? and this has really been a year, hasn‚Äôt it? i need to put my senators on speed dial‚Äîgoodness knows i call them enough. ‚ö°Ô∏è ‚Ä¢

it‚Äôs been powerful and devastating to read so many stories of sexual assault from so many people i love and admire. there isn‚Äôt a woman alive who doesn‚Äôt have a story, whether she tells it aloud or not. we‚Äôve all been sexualized, fetishized, objectified. we‚Äôve all been afraid walking down the street. every one of us. the jackson katz study is circling the internet again (swipe to read) and it‚Äôs so powerfully true. even now, as a 30-year-old on a university campus, i‚Äôm nervous to walk to my car in the dark‚Äîand the first day i met my mentor last year, a woman in her 40s, she told me to be careful in the parking lots at night. mixed in amongst advice about which professors to take and which books to buy was ‚Äúbe careful around here at night,‚Äù not because anything happened to her but because she knew very well that it could. üñ§ ‚Ä¢

medicine is crawling with toxic masculinity. the women around me, in my program and in similar ones, have stories that make my skin crawl. lewd remarks, unwanted physical advances, and worse. last year, after yet another woman confided yet another thing, i told my wife that it‚Äôs not a matter of if it will happen to me but when. it isn‚Äôt the first time for any of us, of course, but it‚Äôs likely also not the last. üíÄ ‚Ä¢

so what do we do in the face of this overwhelming problem? we take one step forward at a time. we stretch out our hands and raise up our voices to mend the part of the world that is within our reach. we believe each other. we stand up for each other. we speak out for each other. together we, the powerful women and the millions of good men, become an antidote that will flush this toxicity from our systems. this may still be a man‚Äôs world, but i‚Äôm #notoneoftheboys. üí•

text:
#snack time.  a little #tuna on #cucumber ü•í slices.  give it a try.  #saturdays and #sundays are my prep days and i have a consistent routine. sat i plan and shop.  sunday i prepare. 
prepare-this is a reeeeeeally important step to having #healthy voice around your house.  i'll often cook at least one meal that is easy to reheat through the week.  i chop all my veggies and put them into pre-portions snacks that are grab-able and easy to throw in my grab bag, and maybe make a batch of #vegan #protein #balls and just set to make the week easier.
the grab bag - this is a bag i encourage everyone to have and bring with them everywhere.  i keep some almonds, an apple, a couple chews, a couple fizz sticks, and tea in it at all times.  then, every morning i can throw in my shaker cup with my shake, and some water, and easily walk out the door!  having supplies with you will help you when temptation comes.  if you've got a healthy alternative on you when you're at that mall, lunchroom, etc...its soooo much easier to resist than when you don't.
note-one thing you should gradually start becoming aware of is what is a portion.  check the next slide for a visual.  we often think "oh this is healthy! i can have as much as i want!" without every really knowing what a proper portion size is.  almonds for example.  they are a great healthy snack option, and a great way to get those important healthy fats, in moderation.  a snack is 10-12 almonds.  its easy to eat 2-3 portions in one sitting if you don't know this, and then wonder why you aren't seeing results if you‚Äôre trying to drop some weight.

text: this. i practiced law for 10 years. while i worked with and along side some incredible people, i was consistently belittled and disrespected as a female attorney on a weekly if not daily basis. when i was a zealous advocate for my client in the same way that my male counterparts were, i was called names like bitch or adjectives like emotional or asked if my blood sugar was low or if it was my time of the month. i had inappropriate jokes and comments made to me- and if i showed offense or spoke up i was labeled as sensitive or a snowflake or a jezebel. i can't imagine if someone had told one of my male partners they were being emotional when they took a stance on something!! that was just how it was. i was supposed to be ok. to get used to it. and guess what? that's how it is in our every day world as well. guess what else? we won't stand for it anymore. the tide is turning. i won't black out my social media tomorrow because i won't silently protest what is going on. i won't be quiet. a black profile photo means nothing to them. but standing our ground loudly will. but not allowing those kinds of comments that we have lived with to happen without a response. but making a scene will. #womenempowerment

#asiargento asia argento says the truth
as promised, here the first release of my new blog "a lingua sciolta '.
in this post, however, i want to deliberately abstain from judging asia, which in reality behind a childhood lived as a daughter of characters rather famous and probably, with little time available to make parents ... with a need to live (with a father horror director) from "child artist", on scary sets, staged in chills, at an age where paradoxically a child can not see a horror film but can interpret it ... with an adolescence made of excesses, drugs and tattoos blasphemous ordinary protagonists (see the holy virgin tattooed on the belly) ... of a controversial and scandalous motherhood, for photos risen during pregnancy (although today on the agenda) ... well, despite what i have followed in these years on the sideboard, because of my interest in morgnan (pseudonym of marco castoldi ex husband, singer and musician and the usual bluvertigo) the feeling a character that i never successful to define!
said there after the 2 interviews previous in the usa and in england, finally stasera has arrived to defend from the accusations of sexual practice on child, to the italian tv on the seven channel, by granting a long interview to massimo giletti.
i do not know where is the truth, i invite the judge who should judging her strongly fitness and / or innocence, but personally i have found it credible, suffering neither contradicting and appreciable for having never taken his reputation always discutable.
in conclusion i find personally more doubts in believing a male who seemed to be sitted to be constructed to sexual performance by a woman which is more than strictly or in any strong physically, without nearly a working role which could achieve what power psychological of submission, in addition to the fact of not being nearly physically pleasing.
concludes with solidarity towards #metoo (born from own silver asia) because nobody can allow you to build a woman!

text: i must say that i find it verrrrry interesting that an unknown woman somewhere had an idea to create a call to action to have women on facebook black out their profile pic for a mere one day as a draw of attention to end sexual assault and domestic abuse, but soooo many ladies see it as ‚Äòdisappearing‚Äô, ‚Äòavoiding‚Äô, ‚Äònot powerful‚Äô, ‚Äònot visible‚Äô, ‚Äòtriggering‚Äô....... it makes me take a deep breath & resign myself to why it‚Äôs hard to create unity and change in the world~ everyone comes from a different point of view & perspective ...... choice & diversity is great..... but why tear down and pull judgement on a call to action that truly was designed to not only bring women together in solidarity on fb  for a few hours, but also, to raise awareness and call attention to a painful and dark matter that has been working its way into the light for countless centuries..... the heavy oppression is  getting looked at! black is visible... black is beautiful... black is all possibilities, and black is the rich soil of soul that allows all creative movements and seeds to grow forth! by doing it together we become noticeable! we couldn‚Äôt see the stars shine if it weren‚Äôt for the darkness..... i refuse to be judged, and made to feel guilt or less bc i‚Äôm taking my profile pic down for a day and making a statement with other resonant beings.... if u don‚Äôt feel called, so be it, but is it really working for the cause to make those who are choosing to go black for a day and take this opportunity as a call to action to have all these other women put out a bunch of postings that are judgmental and critical of this movement as if somehow the ladies choosing this form of action are not in the light or being/staying visible? why not just do ur thing and not criticize? seems like a misunderstanding of intention to me as well as a sad sabotage ...... i respect everyone‚Äôs choice regardless of gender, sexuality, faith, nationality, race for how you want to participate in overturning patriarchal oppression..... i hope we can all just stay open to receive the invitations

text_retweet:
rise of women.

the masculine and feminine energies need each other. we are the yin and the yang. one cannot exist without the other and both are equally important. in mycology, mycorrhizal relationships are symbiotic relationships between a fungi and a plant. the fungi will send chemical signals to the plant as a way to ask for consent before it penetrates. if the plant denies consent, the fungi move on. our society has been based off a parasitic relationship that controls, dominates, and manipulates those who it considers to be inferior. a parasitic infection that penetrates whether or not it has been granted consent. we are infected with a parasite and now is the time to diagnose and heal. we need to switch to a mutually symbiotic relationship where all organisms benefit from the success of the other. the more i learn about biology, the more i realize how important diversity is. the environment suffers when only one organism takes over. this is true in nature as well as our society.
words by: @herbalvisionz

text:
‚Äúdark
eyes in the dark
looking for what?
yours
anything yours, anything ours
all i own
i don‚Äôt want, can‚Äôt be sold.‚Äù - basia bulat
.
.
leaving chicago. i ran into my costar from one of the personal traumas that is always replaying like a movie in the back of my mind-  whenever i‚Äôm in chicago, especially. .
.
i was standing in the rain, in the cold- it doesn‚Äôt bother me, i spent years in chicago without heat. they turned a corner like they do in so many of my dreams, but unlike the conciliatory ghost that has come to feel random and mostly harmless, they were real and just the sight of them flooded all of the memories back. our eyes met and immediately  i ducked under a table. they looked back over their shoulder like they weren‚Äôt sure if they‚Äôd seen me or not. i stayed crouching in the rain until they finally went inside. .
.
they hadn‚Äôt seen me. not the real me. they‚Äôd seen their memory of a girl who was so afraid of herself that she had to drive 100 mph in any direction to outrun her thoughts in the middle of the night. they‚Äôd seen their memory of a girl who apologized *to her assaulter* for ‚Äúbeing mad‚Äù about ‚Äúruining the evening‚Äù. .
.
they never got to know the creature that i am now who walks between worlds and holds their vulnerabilities and their strengths in the same hand. what i love and what i hate about myself both give me courage now. they never got to know the realized version of me.
.
.
luckily, now i mostly think of chicago as a place full of family and friends that i cherish with all of my heart. i even got to see @misscattywompass and @mechanicshopfemme! but running into that person was really hard and sad, especially given all that‚Äôs going on with the kavanaugh hearings. .
.
here‚Äôs my free advice to men- if you‚Äôre not hurting from hearing everyone‚Äôs accounts of the ways they‚Äôve been harmed by rape culture, you are purposefully keeping your heart closed. there is something inside of you that needs to be examined and healed and dealt with. nobody is going around looking for this kind of pain or bending the truth to get a taste of it. nobody. .
.
.
.
.
#metoo #believesurvivors #believewomen #plussizelife #plussizeblogger #darkaesthetic

text:
i am not invisible - but am in the company of thousands just like me. 
we are all the same.
we are gathering with one face, having no color. 
we are ageless and we will not be marginalized.
we are everywhere. even in your dreams. 
we will never be silenced. 
we are speaking out in our 80‚Äôs for the first time and empowering our youth by doing so. so brave. 
we are stronger than we let you think. 
we are our own tribe. 
we will vote you out. 
get ready.

text: a lot of my female clients are coming forward with #metoo experiences. for any female who has been led to experience fear, harassment, assault, embarrassment, belittlement, suppression, less- than, lack of human rights, lack of autonomy, abuse (emotional and physical), neglect, bullying, lack of consent... and sadly the list goes on and on. even sadder: not a single female hasn‚Äôt experienced one of the above or more at some point in life. this isn‚Äôt the way things should be; this shouldn‚Äôt be normalized or swept under the rug. thank you for those coming forward with their powerful accounts. you are survivors, fighters, the strong ones. #consent #womansrightsarehumanrights #womansrights #supportwoman #sisterhood #female #keepyourpoliticsoutofmyuterus #drford #drchristinebaisleyford #thankyoudrblaseyford

text:
if you are a woman who sat quietly through this past week‚Äôs events, admiring others who have spoken out but afraid to do so yourself, i‚Äôm writing to you. you are not alone. i get what you are feeling, and i want to support you through it. because not so long ago, other women supported me through the awful anxiety that gets triggered every time someone in power gets away with being unkind, inappropriate, unjust, and even abusive. .
here is what i want to tell you:
.
maybe you don‚Äôt feel comfortable sharing your own traumatic experiences with others. that‚Äôs ok. maybe you don‚Äôt want to point fingers at your abusers and call them out. that‚Äôs ok, too. maybe your pain and sense of shame is still fresh and raw, or so old that you don‚Äôt even know how to begin to heal it ... that‚Äôs ok. keep taking one moment at a time, reach for help and support, and breathe on. love healed many before you, and it is showing up for you, too.
.
but maybe you also don‚Äôt want to deal with it or talk about it, because you don‚Äôt want to upset your husband, your family or your church community by disagreeing with them - and believing survivors can surely feel to you like betraying them. maybe you are afraid to let them know you are also a survivor who has no evidence because everything happened long ago, or without any witnesses ... because you hear them say nasty things about women survivors and how their only agenda is to ‚Äúruin someone‚Äôs life.‚Äù maybe you are afraid they would yell at you and put you ‚Äúback in your place,‚Äù because that‚Äôs what you‚Äôve learned through the abuse. maybe you are afraid that people you love and depend on (financially or emotionally) will say how your brokenness made you sick and so you are only reacting from a place of hurt and not reason. maybe you are so exhausted from feeling like you have no voice, no brain and absolutely no right to say anything ‚Äì that you‚Äôd rather stay safe in pain than do something about it. .
listen ... that‚Äôs not ok. .
<read more below>

i even let him eat some of it then told him changed my mind and said "no" and he stopped. (see the 2nd and 3rd photos).
his food is exposed; it's not covered.
but i said "no" and he stopped. 
thomas is a dog. a different sex, a different species. but he knows what i mean when i say "no." why is this so difficult of a concept?
